  "root_cause_read": [
    "The AITER compact owner VJP is executable at the target shape, but the current adapter does not materialize a throughput win.",
    "The main measured local-VJP costs are forward recompute, grouped wgrad, xgrad, and prepare_ops. The prepare_ops tax remains about 8 ms median per owner-VJP call even after the transposed-weight LRU cache, suggesting the current cache key does not hit under FSDP/local tensor lifetimes.",
    "This branch still recomputes gate/up/hidden/out_compact in backward instead of consuming compact intermediates exposed by the AITER fused forward.",
    "A hidden AITER grouped-GEMM-only adapter is not enough; the production path needs AITER-forward-compatible saved compact intermediates or a real fused grouped owner-rank training backward."
  ],
  "decision": "Keep the retained saved-dispatch expert_loop canary as the promoted 4x baseline. Keep aiter_compact as an executable diagnostic branch, but do not promote it.",
